<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>INTERNATIONAL&#174; VT 365 DIESEL ENGINE - MANIFOLDS AND EXHAUST GAS RECIRCULATION (EGR) - Removal - Exhaust
        Gas Recirculation Valve
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="S2350302" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="3">
        <title>Exhaust Gas Recirculation Valve</title>
        <figure id="f2350308" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd14/D1406.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 69. EGR valve retaining bolts</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove two M6 x 16 EGR valve retaining bolts.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Turn the EGR valve counter clockwise.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2350309" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd14/D1408.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 70. Removal of EGR valve</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the EGR Valve Puller . The slotted arms slip around the EGR bolt mounting tabs,
                while the other two are positioned over the EGR bolt holes.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2350317" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd14/D1409.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 71. EGR valve removed</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Thread shaft clockwise to remove EGR valve.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, after removing the EGR valve, vacuum loose carbon deposits and debris
                    from inside the intake manifold.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
    </svcproc>
